8.1 WHAT ARE SOLUTIONS?------------------------------------
-----------------------------------------------------------

SOLUTION: A HOMOGENEOUS MIXTURE THAT IS IN ONE STATE.

SOLUTE: WHAT'S BEING DISSOLVED.

SOLVENT: WHAT'S DISSOLVING THE SOLUTE.

-----------------------------------------------------------

PROPERTIES OF SOLUTIONS:

	--> CAN BE SOLID, LIQUID OR GAS
	--> SOLUTE IS DISSOLVED TO THE MOLECULAR OR IONIC LEVEL
			* CANNOT SEE PARTICLES

-----------------------------------------------------------

MOLECULAR SOLUTIONS:
		
	--> COVALENT MOLECULES
	--> DO NOT CONDUCT ELECTRICITY

-----------------------------------------------------------

IONIC SOLUTIONS:

	--> DO CONDUCT ELECTRICITY (BECAUSE IONS ARE CHARGED PARTICLES IN SOLUTION)

-----------------------------------------------------------

